body:
This includes all of #248, along with better tests, significant cleanup of old unused code, and a small fix for `lib64` handling.  I've tested this on Linux (it builds `gcc@5.3.0`, `py-scipy^opebblas`, `py-scipy^netlib-lapack`, and `py-scipy^atlas` fine.  I also tested it with building @eschnett's `gcc@5.3.0` for Mac OS, which I will also merge soon.

I'm about to merge it.

@eschnett: look good to you?
@gartung: Is `-S` handled correctly here for `gcc@4.9.3` on Mac OS?  I would like to get your fix in if possible.
